description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Second Step &lt;/strong&gt;Second Step is a leading mental health charity in the South West offering housing, support and hope to thousands of people with mental health and other needs.  We promote mental health and wellbeing by supporting people and communities to build brighter futures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Second Step, in partnership with ARA, are providing Step Together - an exciting new service in Somerset. It’s for adults who are homeless or are at risk of homelessness with complex needs i.e mental health, substance misuse, behavioural issues, and involvement with in the criminal justice system and significant debt. The service will support clients and work with partners creatively to develop, obtain and sustain housing for the people we support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recovery Coach  1.0 FTE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours          &lt;/strong&gt;37hrs ( 1.0 FTE)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary           &lt;/strong&gt;£19,579 per annum (pro rata)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location       &lt;/strong&gt;Somerset&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working to the Recovery Coach Model principles, you will develop strength-based actions orientated around the Recovery Star.  You will engage and support complex needs service users in leading their journeys, and to maximise their choice and control over the support they receive by developing a responsible network of support. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have an understanding of the issues relating to homelessness, and be able to build and sustain relationships with service users. You will have a commitment to promoting independence and supporting vulnerable people in developing move on and recovery plans. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work in a recovery focused, psychologically informed way (PIE) in all aspects of the team’s practice using relevant interventions, including Assessments, Support Planning, Risk Assessing, Brief Interventions, Critical Time Interventions and Solution Focused Therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive training, and on-going supervision, and be part of our reflective practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like a chat about the role please call either Beverley Richards on 07890 639568 or Rooth Langston-Hart on 07855 014527.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we can offer you;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexi-time working&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Childcare Voucher Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cycle to Work Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;26 days holiday&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An extra days holiday for each year of service up to 5 years&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Second Step is committed to Equal Opportunities and welcomes applicants from all sections of the community and from people who have personal experience of using mental health services.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
